File: They are facing charges of murder, attempted murder and defeating the end of justice.(eNCA/screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Four police officers accused of killing a man during the Wits student protests will apply for bail on Wednesday.
Mthokozisi Ntumba was fatally shot in Braamfontein, as he left a doctor's rooms during the protests. READ: Mthokozisi Ntumba: Police officers remanded in custody The officers are charged with murder, attempted murder and defeating the ends of justice.